  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Barbecued Meat Balls #2</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Meat</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1 1/2</qty>
          <unit>pounds</unit></amt>
        <item>Ground beef</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Barbecue Sauce:</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Minced onion</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>can</unit></amt>
        <item>(2 cups) tomato juice</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Catsup</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar (less if desired)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Vinegar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Worcestershire sauce</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Paprika</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Chili powder</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>dash</unit></amt>
        <item>Ground cloves</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>From:</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Elizabeth Dye &lt;lizdye@SOUTHWIND.NET&gt;</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>Date:</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Sat, 29 Jun 1996 17:41:53 -0500</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Seasoned ground beef with salt and pepper, form into balls and brown on all
  sides in frying pan. Since I got this recipe when my children were small I
  usually used elbow macaroni, it's easier to eat.
  
  Combine ingredients in order given. Simmer while preparing meatballs. When
  meatballs are brown place in sauce and simmere 30 minutes. For variation,
  long precooked spaghetti may be added after meatballs are done.
  
